rom the fundamental studies of the interaction between matter and radiation to the development of devices, components, and systems of tremendous commercial interest for widespread applications in optical telecommunications, medicine, and biotechnology. This book reviews the development of some nonlinear optics researches in China, not only the discovery of new principles, but also potential applications of nonlinear optics for various industries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aLight. 0aNonlinear optics. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Optics & Light.2bisacsh  aEnhanced Field Laser Physics.  aOptical Physics.1 aChen, Xianfeng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChen, Zhigang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeng, Dongmei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuo, Qi, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGuo, Qi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiu, Zhibo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLu, Daquan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRen, Mengxin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShanghai Jiao Tong University Press,.1 aShe, Weilong, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aShe, Weilong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSong, Daohong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTian, Jianguo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aXu, Jingjun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZeng, Heping, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aZeng, Heping, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rel